{"type":"user","uuid":"72452f57-51b0-44e9-8f66-f89e2360eca1","session_id":"fe733541-5377-4442-ae61-1f3bf5281b77","parent_tool_use_id":null,"message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_57361cbcfc28412792bc5c4c","is_error":false,"content":"/usr/lib/python3.11/asyncio/events.py:80: Warning: Unable to fetch server versio\nn: PostgreSQL driver not found. Try running `pip install 'piccolo[postgres]'`\n  self._context.run(self._callback, *self._args)\nUnrecognised command - --help\n\nPiccolo CLI\n===========\nEnter the name of a command followed by --help to learn more.\n\n\nCommands\n--------\napp new\nCreates a new Piccolo app. \n\napp show_all\nLists all registered Piccolo apps. \n\nasgi new\nCreate a basic ASGI app, including Piccolo, routing, and an admin. \n\nfixtures dump\nSerialises the data from the given Piccolo apps / tables, and prints it out.\n\nfixtures load\nReads the fixture file, and loads the contents into the database. \n\nmeta version\nPrints out the Piccolo version. \n\nmigrations backwards\nUndo migrations up to a specific migration. \n\nmigrations check\nLists all migrations which have and haven't ran. \n\nmigrations clean\nIdentifies any rows in the migration table which have no corresponding migration\n module on disk, and then optionally deletes those rows.\n\nmigrations forwards\nRuns any migrations which haven't been run yet. \n\nmigrations new\nCreates a new migration file in the migrations folder. \n\nplayground run\nCreates a test database to play with. \n\nproject new\nCreates a new Piccolo project file (piccolo_conf.py). \n\nschema generate\nAutomatically generates Piccolo Table classes by introspecting the database. Ple\nase check the generated code in case there are errors.\n\nschema graph\nPrints out a graphviz .dot file for your schema. \n\nshell run\nRuns an iPython shell, and automatically imports all of the Table classes from y\nour project.\n\nsql_shell run\nLaunch the SQL shell for the configured engine. For Postgres this will be psql, \nand for SQLite it will be sqlite3.\n\ntester run\nRun your unit test suite using Pytest. While running, it sets the ``PICCOLO_TEST\n_RUNNER`` environment variable to\n``'True'``, in case any other code needs to be aware of this.\n\nuser create\nCreate a new user. \n\nuser list\nList existing users. \n\nuser change_password\nChange a user's password. \n\nuser change_permissions\nChange a user's permissions. \n\nuser list\nList existing users."}]}}
